			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">What's your favourite solo spot for AAs?<a name="44695"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 7 04 12:00 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Now I've finally hit 65, I've been playing about a bit trying to get some AAs. Main places I've tried are:
<br />

<br />
<b>HoH basement:</b>
<br />
Tried chant kiting the humans there, but they took quite some time to die (TDoK, no IM). Used Anglistich's Assonanace (sp?) and 4 dots. 
<br />

<br />
Also tried (briefly) some AE kiting with just 2-3 mobs to get the hang of it. However, I found it very hard to get the range right. Tried this auto-circling thing but it wasn't tight enough. I may go back again and try with lower percussion mods to reduce the run speed.
<br />

<br />
<b>PoN</b>
<br />
When levelling up I spent some time on the nightstalkers here, so I thought they may yield some nice AAs. I've spent quite some time here and the camp is cleared pretty fast, but the xp isn't comparable to an average group in BoT.
<br />

<br />
I then plucked up the courage to try the hobgoblins. After a few deaths early on and the odd accident later, I'm starting to get the hang of this and really like it! Getting 2% per kill pretty much with the hobgoblins. I'm then getting some butterfly adds into the swarms too which helps, as there aren't really enough hobgoblins on their own. This camp has blown me away, the xp vs risk is amazingly good, plus they can drop diamonds, blue diamonds, and some vendor trash items for 85pp or so. Thanks to all those who've posted about it before and have shown me the way. I love getting to highsun those pesky scourges<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
<b>To do</b>
<br />
A few things still to try - 
<br />
1) Mephits. I've heard these are better xp than hobgoblins and a fun challenge, but I've not had the guts to actually try them yet! To be honest they scare me<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" />
<br />

<br />
2) HoH basement - take 2. I'd like to try AE kiting there again and see if I can work it out. But I've heard that it was nerfed by both the EN AA changes and also some mob warping, so a bit unsure on this one.
<br />

<br />
Where do you guys and gals like to go for some quick solo AAs between getting groups? (Please don't all say PoFire or I might cry!! :cry:). Are there any other spots with good AA, some nice drops, or just some good fun to be had where you can fly in for anything from 20 minutes to a few hours?</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=606506">Goldolin</a><br>
Bard of 65 concerts</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
