			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What's your favourite solo spot for AAs?<a name="44718"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 7 04 1:23 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>HoH chant kiting in the basement is decent, will get you an AA every hour and 20 minutes solo. They take about 7 minutes each but give 6-7% AA per kill so its a decent place. I usually do this if I have only an hour to kill.
<br />

<br />
PoN Mephits will be VERY tricky to get to without FM. I remember there was a good guide about doing this camp somewhere but don't know where off top of my head.
<br />

<br />
Nightstalker AAs is about equivalent to chant kiting HoH from my past experiences. The loot at this camp is better though, more consistent. HoH basements can spawn Sentries which drop the Tearshaped Ring rarely and is worth a good deal in the bazaar.
<br />

<br />
I did 6 AAs at Nightstalkers but they are often camped and you have to often sit and wait for respawns.
<br />

<br />
Hobgoblins are fun, I did them for a little while, not much to comment on this camp. Though, if your waiting for repops and aren't afraid of losing your camp, go clear the Gargs. They give the same exp as the hobbies and theres 6 ot 7 of them that are easily pullable from the wall.
<br />

<br />
When I have a lot of time and don't feel like grouping I AE HoH. I do it in the graveyard if no one is there. The humans are not worth AEing, their attack range is too big. Instead, I pull the armors around the garden, usually 10-15 of them. 
<br />

<br />
You can auto-circle these but they DO warp at about 55-60% so its best to stop auto-circling around 70% and switch to manual circles. AA on these is about 3-4% each and takes about 20 minutes. Getting half an AA a kite is nice.
<br />

<br />
Thing is if graveyard is camped you risk training groups and that causes no end of headaches. This is usually my graveyard shift spot when the traffic is low.
<br />

<br />
PoV at the upper level of the castle is nice, can chant kite the geos for 5-6% AA each, they die a little faster than HoH basement mobs. You can AE the Geos as well, I prefer East wall for this, its nice if you can get both WW and EW to yourself, 5-6% AA per and each camp has 5 or 6 geos available. The crawlers have a large melee range, best to just fade if you catch one or chant it down before AEing.
<br />

<br />
Undead in PoV are AEable, but theres a mix of a few undeads that summon so need to beware of those. I personally never did the undead but if your curious could look these up as well.
<br />

<br />
If you have a few hours though and want quick AAs, getting a group in BoT or Tactics shouldnt be too hard and are quite good for exp. HoH basement groups are fast too, I made all 6 AAs of Fading Memories one night in a HoH basement group(about 5-6 hours).
<br />

<br />
</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
