			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: What's your favourite solo spot for AAs?<a name="45144"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 9 04 12:20 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>My favorite spot solo is PON Hobgoblins with a large helping of Nettling Wraith's.  
<br />
I will pull 9 hobs to the plain at the base of the plateau... 
<br />
I then charm a wraith and send back at them as they start to catch up to me.   
<br />
While they fight I add in any nearby wraiths (which I will continue to do as long as I can find them fast enough and still break charm in time)
<br />
Its important to use the wraiths as pets first.. they run faster than hobs.
<br />
Like this I spend some time killing wraiths with a pack of hobs... til all my local wraiths are dead... then I start killing the hobs.
<br />
I let the hobs die out to attrition to give myself a loot opportunity...
<br />
I then go along the river gathering the wraiths further out (and maybe a loathsome creeper for grins)
<br />
Kiting this bunch down give the hobs time to respawn... repeat.
<br />
Doing this I get an AA in 60-80 minutes on average.  This beats many BoT groups for me, tho XP from a tactics group tends to be better.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
