				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Summoner guide?<a name="47209"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jun 20 04 8:10 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>I've been looking for information on mobs that don't summon. I'm still working on my mana pool and ft items, so I only have 2.5 fades per bar, and it takes a long time to replenish.
<br />

<br />
I thought the hobs/wraiths summoned, so I hadn't tried them, although I guess if you are AE kiting you probably still count as being in range most of the time.
<br />

<br />
The WWs in PoN are pretty excellent AA -- about 1.9% per (so every now and again one will only get you 1%).
<br />

<br />
If you choose to swarm kite them, I strongly recommend pulling trees, spiders and birds from just to the side. Personally I keep Song of Dawn loaded for the occasional lucky one that hits me - that's right, hits me. Those HPs will regen and that mob will gain +ve agro vs me. A couple of ticks of Dawn and he's back to fighting my pets.
<br />

<br />
The WWs also drop a variety of diamonds, so the loot is about equivalent on them.
<br />
</span></td>
